               <desc type="site-data" source="#bibl000001-2">Anchan Monastery is located on Anchansi
                  Street, Taigu County (縣城內安禪寺街). It is one of the
                  historical and cultural sites protected at the provincial level. The date of
                  origin is unknown. According to textual sources, it was rebuilt during the Song
                  dynasty, renovated in the Yuan and Ming dynasties, and renovated again in the third year of
                  the Qing Guangxu reign period (1877). The site occupies a total area of over 200
                  square meters and has a north-south orientation, facing south. The subsidiary monastery buildings were destroyed, and
                  currently the only extant structures are the sutra repository (藏经殿) and the main hall (正殿);
                  both of which are axial buildings. While the former appears to be a Song dynasty structure, the
                  latter was built in the Ming dynasty.</desc>
